In Persona 3 Reload, Fuuka is given her own stats, HP/SP bar and Theurgy gauge.

Aside from the Navi skills you can ask her to perform out of battle, her enemy Analysis now has a "High-Analyze" mode which costs 35 SP. https://t.co/t07G8E1kuN

The classic outfits introduced in FES made their way into Persona 3 Reload as obtainable, non-dlc cosmetics. This has not been in a Persona game since P4G as P5 only had paid costumes.

Outfits include School outfits, Butler and Maid outfits, Swimsuits and the Battle Panties. https://t.co/V2h5mA57Ya

Fuuka can use her new SP bar out of battle to perform certain skills.

"Jamming" will make you invisible to shadows on the current floor.

"Sylphid Aura" buffs the party before they start the next fight.

"Shock Noise" inflicts Distress Ailment on the next enemy encounter. https://t.co/Sm5stCiVUr

Besides Monad Doors, Persona 3 Reload also has Monad Corridors. Rather than a singular boss it has many dangerous shadows lurking within. 

At the end is a chest containing valuable items such as weapons, treasure, and NON-DLC cosmetic outfits https://t.co/kk81n5mPiP

Gold Hands in Persona 3 Reload are quick to escape, but if defeated they will provide XP and Money.

Additionally, sometimes Gigantic Golden Hands can spawn, which hold valuable treasure and will drop many items if defeated... https://t.co/UwcQ1OdSki

The Reaper is in Persona 3 Reload and will spawn if you stay on a floor for too long.

It is very powerful and will absolutely demolish an unprepared team, so if you are still at a low level, don't hesitate to just run away. https://t.co/ONuOGwDrUT
